<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>groups</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>

<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>groups</REFNAME>

<REFPURPOSE>
Modify a group
</REFPURPOSE>

</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<SYNOPSIS>
groups [user]
</SYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<REFSECT1INFO>
<DATE>27 February 2000</DATE>
</REFSECT1INFO>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
groups displays the current group ID names or values.  If the value
does not have a corresponding entry in /etc/group, the value will be
displayed as the numerical group value.  The optional user parameter
will display the groups for the named user.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>

